# Campus Connect – MVP Spec

## 1. One-line description
Campus Connect is a college-only social app with exclusive email login, anonymous confessions, a “tea” gossip feed, and a campus bulletin for useful updates.

## 2. User types
- Student (main user)
- Faculty (optional, uses bulletin mostly)

## 3. Features in MVP

1. Auth (.edu only)
   - Signup with college email + password
   - Login
   - View own profile

2. Profile
   - Fields: name, email, branch, year, bio, relationship_status
   - Edit profile

3. Anonymous Confessions
   - Post anonymous text confession
   - See confessions feed (most recent)
   - Upvote confessions

4. Tea Section (Anonymous Gossip)
   - Post anonymous “tea” text
   - See tea feed (most recent)
   - Upvote tea posts

5. Campus Bulletin (Named Posts)
   - Post bulletin (title + content, not anonymous)
   - See bulletin feed (latest posts)

6. Search Users
   - Search by name
   - Result shows name, branch, year, bio (no email)

## 4. Screens

1. Login / Signup
2. Home (tabs or buttons to: Confessions, Tea, Bulletin)
3. Confessions Feed + Create Confession
4. Tea Feed + Create Tea Post
5. Bulletin Feed + Create Bulletin
6. My Profile + Edit Profile
7. Search Users

## 5. Database (simplified)

### users
- id
- name
- email
- password_hash
- branch
- year
- bio
- relationship_status
- created_at

### anonymous_posts
- id
- user_id
- type (`confession` or `tea`)
- content
- upvotes
- created_at

### bulletin_posts
- id
- user_id
- title
- content
- created_at

## 6. APIs (basic)

### Auth
- POST /api/auth/register
- POST /api/auth/login
- GET /api/auth/me

### Users
- GET /api/users/me
- PUT /api/users/me
- GET /api/users?search=query

### Anonymous posts
- GET /api/anon?type=confession
- GET /api/anon?type=tea
- POST /api/anon  (body: { type, content })
- POST /api/anon/:id/upvote

### Bulletin
- GET /api/bulletin
- POST /api/bulletin
- GET /api/bulletin/:id